                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)Turkey/1010: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-23T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 23, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 25—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>739. With reference to my 717, April 21, the British Ambassador informed me last
                    night that he had satisfied himself in the course of a talk with the Minister of
                    Foreign Affairs that the prohibition of the further export of chrome from Turkey
                    would not apply to shipments to Great Britain and the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
